## üöÄ Quick Start

### Prerequisites

- Node.js 18+ 
- npm, yarn, or pnpm
- [Supabase CLI](https://supabase.com/docs/guides/cli) (for backend){{#includeMobile}}
- Xcode (for iOS development)
- Android Studio (for Android development){{/includeMobile}}

### Installation

```bash
# Install dependencies
{{PACKAGE_MANAGER}} install

# Set up your environment
cp .env.example .env
# Edit .env with your configuration
```

### Configuration

Edit `.env` with your service configurations:

```bash
# Required: Supabase
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=your_supabase_project_url
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_supabase_anon_key
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your_service_role_key{{#includeSubscriptions}}

# Stripe (for subscriptions)
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=your_stripe_secret_key
VITE_STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=your_stripe_publishable_key
STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=your_webhook_secret{{/includeSubscriptions}}{{#includeNotifications}}{{#resendEmail}}

# Resend (for email)
RESEND_API_KEY=your_resend_api_key
RESEND_FROM_EMAIL=noreply@yourdomain.com{{/resendEmail}}{{#sendgridEmail}}

# SendGrid (for email)
SENDGRID_API_KEY=your_sendgrid_api_key
SENDGRID_FROM_EMAIL=noreply@yourdomain.com{{/sendgridEmail}}{{/includeNotifications}}
```

### Database Setup

1. Create a new Supabase project at [supabase.com](https://supabase.com)
2. Run the database migrations:

```bash
# Initialize Supabase locally
supabase init

# Link to your project
supabase link --project-ref your-project-ref

# Push database schema
supabase db push

# Deploy Edge Functions
supabase functions deploy
```

### Development

```bash
# Start development server
{{PACKAGE_MANAGER}} run dev

# Open http://localhost:5173
```{{#includeMobile}}

### Mobile Development

